article.headline: Coastal Carolina 80, Gardner-Webb 64
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS N.C. -- Chad Gray scored 18 points to help Coastal Carolina defeat Gardner-Webb 80-64 on Saturday night. Joseph Harris added a double-double with 14 points and 11 rebounds and Kierre Greenwood scored 17 points as the Chanticleers (16-2, 6-0 Big South) won their 12th straight. Coastal Carolina used a 7-4 run to take a 31-25 lead on Chad Gray's free throw with 5:18 to play in the first half. The Chanticleers, who led 38-35 at halftime, opened the second half on a 13-6 run. Logan Johnson's layup put Coastal Carolina up 51-41 with 15:06 remaining. Logan Johnson added 11 points for the Chanticleers, which improved to 6-0 in the Big south for the first time since 1990-91. The six victories also gave Coastal Carolina one more conference win than it had last season. Jonathan Moore scored 19 points for the Runnin' Bulldogs (4-11, 1-4) and Anton Silver added 14.
